main event: A bright starlike object was observed for 20 minutes in Eaton, Ohio on November 6, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as similar to a turning light and its side.
An Air Force jet was sent to investigate but was unable to locate the object.
Information about the object's elevation, azimuth, and how it disappeared was not provided.
The observers were likely watching a star or planet, but the case is being carried as insufficient data.
The observers were asked to complete a questionnaire with additional details about the sighting.
